eant by QM Jonathan Bull; served to close of the war. At Danbury Alarm; at New Haven (BTL018); at Battle of Saratoga (BTL011). Pensioned. Pension File No. 9153.","war_id":"WAR004"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Lt.-Col. Isaac Cowles","first_name":"Isaac","last_name":"Cowles","title":"Lt.-Col.","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"military","header":"He fought from Long Island to Saratoga","body":"Isaac Cowles rose from sergeant to lieutenant-colonel commandant of the 15th Connecticut Militia during the Revolution. He saw action at the Battle of Long Island, the Danbury and New Haven alarms, and Saratoga.","number":1},{"category":"business","header":"Afterward he kept a Farmington tavern","body":"Back home in Farmington, Cowles farmed his father's homestead and kept a tavern, prospering into a man of local standing. A federal pension file recorded his long Revolutionary service.","number":2}],"slug":"isaac-cowles-1756"},"H00309":{"id":"H00309","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":5,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1758,"month":3,"day":11,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00104","mother_id":"I00136"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 309"}],"death":{"year":1817,"month":4,"day":5,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM004","plot_notes":"Gravestone confirmed"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00270","children_ids":["H00697","H00698","H00699","H00700","H00701","H00702","H00703"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1781,"date_month":12,"date_day":27}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_n